Hello NEAT users,

I know there's a python version of NEAT not listed in Ken's website.
Searching for 'python' on the group's history I found some threads
about it from 2004-2005. I contacted the author (Karl Lewin) and the
guy (Thomas) who was asking for the source code, but received no
replies (I'm not even sure they use the same e-mail).

Web archive last Karl's website record is from 2005, but the source
file (pyn.zip) is not available.

Does anyone have the code or is it lost forever?

@Ken, wouldn't it be nice to list the python version on the website
(given Karl's permission)?

Thanks,
Cesar
